
[1]suavity

   SUAVITY, n. [L.]

   1. Sweetness, in a literal sense. [Not in use.]

   2. Sweetness, in a figurative sense; that which is to the mind what
   sweetness is to the tongue; agreeableness; softness; pleasantness; as
   suavity of manners; suavity of language, conversation or address.
